                <h2 scrollto-destination="12857661" data-legacyid="s3" id="12857661" data-section-title="Preserving ancient woodland" class="section-title jumplink-heading">Preserving ancient woodland</h2>
            <div >
                <div id="12857662" class="article-section-wrapper js-article-section js-content-section  " data-section-parent-id="12857661">
                    
                    <p>Ancient woodlands are some of the rarest and most biodiverse habitats in the UK and home to more threatened species than any other terrestrial habitat in the country. We will be funding the restoration of nearly 12 hectares of degraded temperate rainforest over the next two years in partnership with the Woodland Trust. Great Knott Wood is located on the shore of Lake Windermere within the Lake District National Park. Restoration efforts include the protection of veteran trees and deadwood, removal of non-native species, and the gradual thinning of the canopy to carefully increase light levels. Together, these activities will help counteract biodiversity loss and protect these habitats for future generations.</p>
                </div>
                <div id="12857663" class="article-section-wrapper js-article-section js-content-section  " data-section-parent-id="12857661">
                    
                    <a id = "12857663" scrollto-destination="12857663"></a><div data-id="BIO059877F3" class="fig fig-section"><div class="graphic-wrap"><a reveal-id="BIO059877F3" data-open="BIO059877F3" class="fig-link"><img class="content-image" src="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/bio/12/3/10.1242_bio.059877/2/m_bio05987703.png?Expires=1716455205&amp;Signature=dM73crmiOMiXJST~Acm9NS0ZywDQdE5-seusqPHztZFtDT8qeYNzSvhDJuNqtOpieyrDocYuqwZfc47KOQWHTxgf5ApulKGNSlt0OJm89T7xkMuQT6CFcQvtNyjdYJbEjKSjZAwyk99TS-7-6xTXwIl3~dB35AFzep4wZymwWjEYovucYxqmqq-kdrFL~TeSUDKpNg3vFoDVKiWsoJGdskE1ju-hJYFEoLPEqsMCuhn254QNOnB-ePoBdY5XbA5QzCUapA0p25ag8trkvYJSUccvWGGz7NMDb~kRyOgYCn9BuKMf6Cu8Z2cDD68TFL4jpKxW30N-Fi6Lnft7vsOYPw__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA" data-src="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/bio/12/3/10.1242_bio.059877/2/m_bio05987703.png?Expires=1716455205&amp;Signature=dM73crmiOMiXJST~Acm9NS0ZywDQdE5-seusqPHztZFtDT8qeYNzSvhDJuNqtOpieyrDocYuqwZfc47KOQWHTxgf5ApulKGNSlt0OJm89T7xkMuQT6CFcQvtNyjdYJbEjKSjZAwyk99TS-7-6xTXwIl3~dB35AFzep4wZymwWjEYovucYxqmqq-kdrFL~TeSUDKpNg3vFoDVKiWsoJGdskE1ju-hJYFEoLPEqsMCuhn254QNOnB-ePoBdY5XbA5QzCUapA0p25ag8trkvYJSUccvWGGz7NMDb~kRyOgYCn9BuKMf6Cu8Z2cDD68TFL4jpKxW30N-Fi6Lnft7vsOYPw__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA" alt="Preservation and restoration of ancient woodland at Great Knott Wood, Lake Windermere." path-from-xml="BIO05987703.tif" /></a><div class="fig-orig original-slide"><a section="12857663" class="fig-view-orig" href="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/bio/12/3/10.1242_bio.059877/2/bio05987703.png?Expires=1716455205&amp;Signature=zPkPXMvY73EVMBsR0AxAacvii6f8Mbm6ZaRi7DElHqGk~cuB~pjH8mWt1xtf3hKEBwG0~AblZ5~09ER54ePmrhWw0aa3EL77xLzaTb~mXhEa6Bffbq6pZMEGhRNiB4ixazulVw2tx-UEXohWEx7C8CTThvPep~Mc-Rp3xxSlhT0rMOopMb74bVZMTIevEzOOxr1ERkuKzMmeW17Lb42pXfTUeMklOWgGtbiw5dmp30Wbq2Osol~a0v6jvH-B9TwsYtjd-oFA9UVzfG1xd0NHjjhBcfB49ZoaoknNk~DOMsgjwwW3b2-MRLQVNJ25rGohYm7Ey1APlD7E8jvS